}
```
* Wait a few rounds of getting the error and then kill the running **netcat** process.

The above code should continue to produce the same **EADDRINUSE** error until you kill the parent.  In the **OUTPUT** below I killed **netcat** off about half way through and verified with **netstat -an** that the port was no longer bound.  **netcat** can easily rebind the port if started up again, and all the **strace** data from the node server shows that it will never attempt the bind() again.

